                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.5212/13.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 11, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 11 received too late to notify Commander of battleship.
                    However, on receipt telegram from Brazilian Minister early afternoon secured
                    assurances authorities to accord decent treatment Spanish Minister. He arrived
                    safely 10.40 tonight, immediately went on board Spanish transatlantic steamer
                    which sails 16th. If necessary, refuge on board American battleship will be
                    arranged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
